# AI workflow

This rule governs **agent behavior**, complementing
[`workflow.mdc`](mdc:.cursor/rules/workflow.mdc) which governs the
human-or-agent dev loop.

## Plan before multi-file changes

If a task touches more than one file, switch to plan mode (or write a
plan inline in the response) before editing. Surface trade-offs; do not
silently pick one. See `c:\Users\Brandon\.cursor\rules\planner-first.mdc`.

## When to spawn a subagent

| Spawn a subagent when…                              | Use                       |
|-----------------------------------------------------|---------------------------|
| Exploring an unfamiliar area broadly                | `explore` (built-in)      |
| Running a discrete implementation task in isolation | `developer` (built-in)    |
| Planning before implementation                      | `planner` (built-in) or `.cursor/agents/planner.md` |
| Domain-specific work in this project                | One of `.cursor/agents/<name>.md`: `research`, `signal`, `strategy`, `backtest`, `risk`, `evaluation`, `monitoring`, `reviewer` |

The custom agents in `.cursor/agents/` carry the trading-lab guardrails
(no LLM in execution, all orders through risk, etc.). Prefer them over
generic `developer`/`generalPurpose` for project-domain work.

## Risk and reviewer agents are gatekeepers, not editors

- `risk` agent (`readonly: true`) reads strategy / config files and
  approves or rejects. It cannot edit `risk/engine.py`.
- `reviewer` agent (`readonly: true`) writes proposals to
  `.cursor/state/proposed/` for humans to ratify. It does not touch
  `.cursor/rules/` directly.

This is the project's self-improvement contract: agents propose, humans
ratify via `DECISIONS.md`.

## Definition of done for agent work

The same as [`workflow.mdc`](mdc:.cursor/rules/workflow.mdc):

- Acceptance criteria met with cited evidence.
- `pytest`, `ruff`, `mypy` green.
- A `SESSION_LOG.md` entry written by the `append_session_log` hook.
- If an architectural decision shifted, a `DECISIONS.md` entry written
  manually (the hook only proposes).

## Forbidden in agent output

- "should work", "left as an exercise", "verified offline" without a
  command + result citation.
- Marking a task complete before tests pass.
- Editing rules under `.cursor/rules/` based on hook signal alone.
  Rule changes require a `DECISIONS.md` entry by a human.
